festival.introText:
Cafe Mambo Ibiza lands in Warwickshire for an un-missable festival level party at the incredible Warwick Castle!

The Ibiza brand takeover the iconic Warwick Castle site for an evening of Ibiza classics. The exciting Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics is dedicated to evoking memories of Ibiza's golden years, firmly focusing on the feel good vibes and celebrating the music that makes Ibiza the party capital of the world.

For over 25 years Cafe Mambo Ibiza has become an institution, best known for its stunning sunsets, special guest DJs & parties - the Ibiza venue has become a right of passage for any reveler to experience on the magical White Isle.

Taking place at the the Warwick Castle Site with a unique setting & Festival set-up. Expect surprises & spectacular production accompanied by the very best Ibiza inspired soundtrack.

Expect the unexpected with Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics!

THE LINE-UP

ROGER SANCHEZ

JUDGE JULES

LOVELY LAURA & BEN SANTIAGO

JULIE MCKNIGHT (Live PA)

SONIQUE (Live PA)

LOECA

Food from Digbeth Dining Club

 

Book Your Tickets Now!

faqs.question: When is Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics at Warwick Castle?
faqs.answer: Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics at Warwick Castle takes place on Saturday 13th May 2023.

faqs.question: Is there parking on site?
faqs.answer: There is no parking on site. We encourage you to use public transport or local taxi firms as we have great pick up and drop off facilities on site.

faqs.question: How much are tickets?
faqs.answer: General Access Tickets are priced from £30.00+bf to £45.00+bf. There are limited VIP tickets available too, these are priced from £75.00+bf to £90.00+bf.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer: The event is on a field with disabled access & disabled facilities. Please contact the festival if you would like to book a space at their disability friendly stage viewing point away from crowds. This is at no extra charge. Please contact info@newvisionevents.co.uk to find out more.

faqs.question: Is onsite camping available?
faqs.answer: No, Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics at Warwick Castle is a one day, non-camping festival and no camping equipment is needed.

faqs.question: Where is Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics at Warwick Castle?
faqs.answer: Cafe Mambo Ibiza Classics at Warwick Castle takes place at Warwick Castle on the Pageant Field.

faqs.question: Road closure & drop off system
faqs.answer: Road closures may be in place at the end of the event on Stratford Road and Branbury Road. Please use the main town centre for drop off and pick up.

faqs.question: What is included with the VIP?
faqs.answer: VIP Tickets include fast track entry, access to the VIP village with extra bars, cocktail bar, chill out area, posh loos and access to the VIP stage viewing platform.

faqs.question: What are the opening times for the main event?

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: How old do I need to be to attend and will I need ID?
faqs.answer: You will need to be 18 or older. There is a challenge-25 policy upon entry and at all bars, if you look younger than 25, please bring ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring food & drink into the event?
faqs.answer: Sadly not.. but the festival does have fully stocked bars selling all your favourite alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks & award-winning food stalls on site from Digbeth Dining Club.

faqs.question: What can I bring / not bring?
faqs.answer:
Can I bring a bag?

Yes you can bring a small bag, this will be searched upon entry (We class small bags as no larger than 35cm x 40cm x 19cm). The event does not allow large bags.

Can I bring Camping chairs, umbrellas & blankets?

You can't bring Camping Chairs or umbrellas - small blankets are ok.

Can I bring in flags or banners?

You can't bring flags or banners. Laser Pens are also not permitted.

Can I bring animals or pets?

Animals or pets are not permitted at the event, with the exception of registered assistance dogs.

Can we bring sun cream with us?

Yes, but no glass bottles.

Can we bring Perfume / Deodorant?

Glass Bottles / Aerosols are Banned. Roll On Deodorant is fine.

Is there anywhere to charge my phone?

Sadly not, but we’re looking into this for next year.

faqs.question: Is there a dress code?
faqs.answer: It’s a Festival style event, go wild!

faqs.question: Who is performing?
faqs.answer: This is an evening of live performances & DJ sets. DJ's include Roger Sanchez & Judge Jules as well as live performances from Lovely Laura, Sonique & Julie Mcknight. More artists & surprises to be announced too.

faqs.question: Is the event outside?
faqs.answer: This is a festival style event and is open air.

faqs.question: Will you be releasing the set times?
faqs.answer: Full Set times will be released before the event.
